reviews.title: Too bad!
reviews.text: Run away! Asked if we could order something, after a few minutes, but chatting with your colleague, is more important. And if the place is packed, you have a point. Her answer, however, was an exasperated one: "I'll be right there." Then we quit and just heard the following: "Are you kidding me, are they running away?" Yeah, we're walking away. I come for a drink completely voluntarily and find it very strange that I am not helped! And I mean it again! Success

reviews.title: Burnt shrimp
reviews.text: Yesterday I had dinner at levels with my granddaughter and I had ordered fish and chips but the shrimp were very burned so I say that to the staff and they say I will pass it on to the kitchen and otherwise she did nothing with it bit too bad.....

reviews.title: Share & diner or lunch
reviews.text:
Delicious all snacks and drinks bites ordered and feasting together 
The choice is huge and very tasty 
The bitterballen are also particularly good

reviews.title: Beautiful restaurant in beautiful Harlingen
reviews.text:
Had a lovely lunch here last week. 
My wife was particularly pleased with the fish & chips, which goes off the beaten track and was very tasty. 

Furthermore, friendly service and a beautiful business that requires some attention here and there.

reviews.title: Just enjoy it.
reviews.text: A good place to enjoy the good food, drinks and good very friendly service. The food was excellent and very tasty.

reviews.title: Perfect! Long time since we have eaten so delicious in a grand cafe / restaurant
reviews.text:
Upon entering it is indeed very noisy and fairly noisy but you get used to that. After all, it's a grand cafe on a Saturday night 5:30.
A few talk laugh or scream louder than necessary but you have that everywhere. 

We 2 (46) and son (18) really enjoyed our meal there. 
Before head and after. 
Starter rib fingers and tasting for 2 and as head we had steak/Scandinavian meats/levels hair salon. 
Dessert tasting for 2 and hot cheesecake. 
In addition, various delicious cocktails and drinks. 

Everything was well seasoned, deliciously baked and nice and warm where it needed to be warm. 
Waiting time was in our opinion fine for how busy it was.

0.0 complaints. 
We will definitely be back❤

reviews.title: Very disappointed
reviews.text: The waitress who helped us initially was not very talkative. And then, to make matters worse, she dropped a full tray of red wine over my coat. Anything could happen, but there was no excuse. And I just had to throw white wine over my coat, angry I walked to the bar, there I was kindly spoken to and the dry cleaning costs would be paid. Everything neatly emailed through but so far nothing received. Too bad I'm very disappointed in Levels.

mgmtResponse.text:
Hoi Siemona, dankjewel voor je review. We betreuren je ervaring zoals ook telefonisch aangegeven. We gaan er van uit dat de jas inmiddels weer hersteld is in de oude staat na een ritje naar de stomerij. We hebben dit met de dame in kwestie besproken. Die gaf aan erg geschrokken te zijn en vond het lastig om met zo'n soort situatie om te gaan. We gaan er met ons team aan werken. We hopen je snel weer eens te zien bij Levels. 

Groetjes Angela & team de rest van Team Levels

reviews.title: Quality food very moderate
reviews.text: During the fishing days on recommendation here dinner taken in the evening. Nice seats. Too bad the DJ left the volume knob at maximum. Have asked to sit inside with 3 people. Had seen there was a table open. According to staff occupied. So I took a spot outside. Apart is that the rest of the evening the table in restaurant remained empty! Menu with surprising ingredients. It took a while for the dishes to come to the table. Of the 3 different dishes, only the hairdressing salon Levens could handle it.

mgmtResponse.text:
Hoi Eric, 

We begrijpen helaas niet zo goed dat we dit hier én op Google 5 weken later nog terug moeten lezen. We hadden liever gehad dat we er iets aan hadden kunnen doen en dat gaat nu lastig.... Dat de tafel binnen niet beschikbaar was, komt door de drukte zoals je gemerkt hebt, anders had het eten 'nog' langer geduurd. Wij hebben een keuken die geen 250 mensen tegelijkertijd kan voorzien van eten, we moeten dus keuzes maken met zulke drukke dagen. Dat is net als de menu kaart, die maken we kleiner in verband met de drukte tijdens de Visserijdagen. 

Wat betreft de DJ weet die zeker wel waar de volumeknop zit, deze lieve man doet gewoon wat van hem gevraagd wordt. Er zijn genoeg 'rustige' terrasjes tijdens de visserijdagen, wij kiezen er juist voor om een bepaalde sfeer te creëren en daar hou je van of niet. Dat zorgt dat bepaalde mensen graag plaats nemen en anderen door lopen, dat is een keuze die wij als bedrijf zijnde maken en dat is ook iets waar je voor kiest op het moment dat je bij ons op terras gaat zitten. Dat geld ook voor elke laatste zondag van de maand, ook dan is het Lazy Lounge. 

Fijn dat in ieder geval de kapsalon goed gesmaakt heeft. Inmiddels is er weer een uitgebreide en heerlijke menu kaart met herfst en winter gerechten. Wie weet tot ziens maar dan dit keer niet tijdens een Lazy Lounge middag/avond. 

We wensen Eric in ieder geval een fijn weekend. 

Groetjes Angela & team.

reviews.title: Nice terrace with great food.
reviews.text: Nice large terrace with comfortable seating. Attentive service. Menu with nice dishes, slightly different. Served nicely. Delicious wine. Very pleasant stay.

reviews.title: Pavement eating at its best.
reviews.text:
A lovely pavement restaurant where we stopped for drinks in the morning. In the afternoon we returned for lunch. Not speaking Dutch, we had to have a guess with the menu. We ended up with a chicken burger and fries, the chicken having a tasty coating. Also a pulled pork burger which was also delicious. 
   The staff were friendly and helpful. There was shelter round the tables on the pavement, leading to comfortable outside eating. A great find.

reviews.title: Cozy place, friendly staff, great menu
reviews.text:
Cozy decor, prompt and friendly staff.

In terms of decoration, it is cozy and warm, but the acoustics are somewhat difficult to understand when it is busier.

The menu is excellent and has a wide choice, but the preparation is not really special. It is quite cool and in terms of decoration and garnish it is really minimal for what you pay.

All in all, we had a nice, excellent meal.

reviews.title: Noise at Levels during dinner.
reviews.text: There appeared to be a disc jockey present who played music. Unfortunately, it was quite loud, so it took a lot of energy to have a conversation. The staff responded understandingly to our complaint, but nothing changed. It would say on the website that this happens once in a while, but I have not seen it and do not see it yet.

tips.body: Vraag even na of er een discjockey is als je niet van harde muziek houdt tijdens het eten.

reviews.title: Nice cozy warm place to have a drink
reviews.text:
Yes, delicious high wine with sister-in-law (birthday)
Nice planks with every wine
.
It was way too much... but I enjoyed it and paid too much because it was so busy, but it was refunded with apologies...

Top business with an eye for people..

reviews.title: Top opportunity with terrace
reviews.text: Lots of choice. Good food, nice place, quick service. Nice staff. Can eat on the terrace. Absolutely great.

reviews.title: Great coffee, with a smile
reviews.text:
Lovely bar/restaurant, well decorated with a great ambience.

Staff are friendly and provide great service.

I've been there several times for coffee and they make lovely Cortado, Cappuccinos and espressos.

With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Experience Santa Fe: art, flavor & fun on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Whether you enjoy nature hikes or margarita trails (or both!), you'll want to embrace everything Santa Fe has to offer. Its unique mix of big-city culture, small-town charm, and Southwestern flavor has earned it the nickname "The City Different." Whatever you're into—from art to opera to world-class restaurants—Santa Fe offers a chance to escape the everyday.

seoInfo.metaDescription: Cusco will definitely leave you breathless. At more than 11,000 feet above sea level, this ancient city’s steep cobbled streets make even the fittest travelers gasp for air, though a cup of coca tea is the local cure-all. Once the hub of the mighty Inca Empire, Cusco now pulses with a deep sense of history and culture. I’m forever in awe of its unique blend of ancient ruins and grand Spanish colonial architecture. My recommendation: take your time—there's no rush in this city where every corner tells a story.

tripContent.title: Enter the unknown: Nevada’s wildest hidden realms
tripContent.description: Strange, surreal, and totally unforgettable, this is Nevada off the rails. From alien highways to haunted hotels, and from outdoor art playgrounds to eccentric ghost towns, this route is made for the curious traveler. Embrace the uncommon and uncover a different side of the Silver State, where ever stop feels like a secret waiting to be stumbled upon.

reviews.title: A tasty burger
reviews.text: If you want a tasty burger and refreshing pint this is the place, couldn’t fault it.  Nicely furnished establishment with pretty good service.

reviews.title: Cozy, friendly, super tasty food and COCKTAILS
reviews.text: We had been to the Levels Restaurant and Cocktailbar before but also this time it was great to enjoy again. Nice new dishes on the menu but also the "make your own Burger" and a real cocktail shaker behind the bar. Guaranteed a pleasant evening. Thank you Levels and see you next time. We'll be back soon.

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.text: Such a great restaurant, with comfortable seats and a modern design. I created my own hamburger which was really good, the servants/bartender were really friendly and helpful. overall, good service and in my opinion one of the best restaurants/bars in Harlingen.

reviews.title: Service and quality sub par
reviews.text: Beef burger was good. Salad dressing without any taste. Chicken burger too spicy for kids and beer bottle not cold. Really disappointed

reviews.title: Mediocre
reviews.text: The food at this restaurant was only ok, I had the special and was far from special. I could have easily made it at home and I am not a cook.. also the service was just normal, people were nice which I appreciate BUT not knowledgeable.  Our waitress didn’t know what the special was. At least you should know what that is and what’s in it.. but she didn’t. They should also study up on gin and tonics.. Hendricks gin is served with cucumber, not lime..

reviews.title: Best burger and egg special in Frisland
reviews.text:
We walked around empty Harlingen when we found this place. You can completely customise you burger and eggs. Nice and cold beers and comfortable interior.

Please fellow travelers in Harlingen, just go there and be served by that wonderful Indonesian guy that works there.

reviews.title: Big balls!
reviews.text:
My friend and I decided to go for a drink and some 'bitterballen' (a Dutch snack of a meat-based fried ball with a roux of veal or beef) on the terrace of Levels a couple of weeks ago. We each had a lovely (though quite expensive) mocktail and huge balls (the bitterballen of course). 
The only thing I didn't like was that our drinks came out (way) after our bitterballen did. And because of the size of them, we needed drinks! (This is turning into a weird review, isn't it?)
Even though they say size matters, I would probably like the bitterballen to be a bit smaller because I felt like the roux was a bit too dry (I think that is probably necessary in order for the balls to stay in one piece when you fry them). 
Let's end this review in style... The drinks were pretty classy when we did get them ;)

reviews.title: Best place in Harlingen! Good food, friendly service and nice atmosphere!!!
reviews.text:
Really, I have been many times now and every time it has been very good all round.

I can only recommend even if you are looking for fresh vegetarian food it has a few things but always a changing dish that has been very delicious, nicely presented and made from fresh ingredients.

The burgers are good too and you can configure your own choice of toppings and sources. Also a good selection of vines!

Its a very comfortable, spacious and tastefully arranged modern style bistro restaurant that can give the more established places in Harlingen a run for their money!

I will be there many more times I hope...

LEKKER & LEUK!!!
